Story*

Once upon a time, in a forest there lived a monkey who resided on a berry tree which was on the banks of the river.
In the same foresr there lived a Crocodile and his wife.
One day, the Crocodile came to the banks of the river and rested under the tree.
The kind hearted monkey offered him some fruits.
The crocodile came back the next day for more fruits as he loved them.
As the day passed by, the crocodile and the monkey became good friends.

One day the monkey send some fruits for the crocodile's wife, she ate the fruits and loved them but was jealous 
as she did not like her husband spending time with a monkey. 
She told her husband that "if the fruits are so juicy, i wonder how sweet the monkey's heart will be." 
She told that she wanted to get her the heart of the monkey. 
The crocodile was not willing to kill his friend but no choice.